Here's the XAML and ViewModel setup:

**XAML**

```xml
<RefreshView IsRefreshing="{Binding IsRefreshing}"
             Command="{Binding RefreshCommand}">
    <CollectionView ItemsSource="{Binding Items}"
                    SelectionMode="Single"
                    SelectedItem="{Binding CurrentItem, Mode=TwoWay}"
                    SelectionChangedCommand="{Binding ItemSelectedCommand}">
        <CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
            <DataTemplate x:DataType="models:Item">
                <Grid Padding="12" ColumnDefinitions="48,*">
                    <Image Source="{Binding Icon}"
                           WidthRequest="40" HeightRequest="40" />
                    <Label Grid.Column="1"
                           Text="{Binding Name}"
                           VerticalOptions="Center" />
                </Grid>
            </DataTemplate>
        </CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
        <CollectionView.EmptyView>
            <ContentView>
                <Label Text="No items found."
                       HorizontalOptions="Center"
                       VerticalOptions="Center" />
            </ContentView>
        </CollectionView.EmptyView>
    </CollectionView>
</RefreshView>
```

**ViewModel**

```csharp
public partial class ItemsViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    private readonly IApiService _api;
    private readonly INavigation _navigation;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private ObservableCollection<Item> items = new();

    [ObservableProperty]
    private Item? currentItem;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool isRefreshing;

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task Refresh()
    {
        try
        {
            var data = await _api.GetItemsAsync();
            MainThread.BeginInvokeOnMainThread(() =>
            {
                Items.Clear();
                foreach (var item in data)
                    Items.Add(item);
            });
        }
        finally
        {
            IsRefreshing = false; // Must set false to dismiss spinner
        }
    }

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task ItemSelected()
    {
        if (CurrentItem is null) return;

        await _navigation.PushAsync(new DetailPage(CurrentItem));

        CurrentItem = null; // Reset so the same item can be re-selected
    }
}
```

**Key bindings explained:**

| Property | Binding | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `IsRefreshing` | `TwoWay` (default on `RefreshView`) | Drives the refresh spinner; set `false` when done |
| `Command` on `RefreshView` | `RefreshCommand` | Fires your API reload logic |
| `SelectedItem` | `CurrentItem`, `Mode=TwoWay` | Tracks the selected item in the ViewModel |
| `SelectionChangedCommand` | `ItemSelectedCommand` | Triggers navigation when selection changes |
| `ItemsSource` | `ObservableCollection<Item>` | **Must** be `ObservableCollection`, not `List`, so adds/removes update the UI |

**Important details:**
- **Reset `CurrentItem` to `null`** after navigation so the user can tap the same item again.
- **Set `IsRefreshing = false`** in a `finally` block to guarantee the spinner dismisses, even on errors.
- **Update collections on the UI thread** via `MainThread.BeginInvokeOnMainThread`.
- **Never use `ViewCell`** — the `Grid` root in the template is correct.
- Set `x:DataType` on `DataTemplate` for compiled bindings and better performance.
